{
  "texts": [
    "Agents must navigate environments with objects that have specific activation requirements, and success depends on their coordinated timing and teamwork.",
    "Each room offers unique challenges that demand effective team collaboration and strategic planning.",
    "For example, a basic task may require two agents to press switches at different locations simultaneously to open a door.",
    "Further details and visual representations of each scenario can be found in Appendix B.3.",
    "Meanwhile, the State Manager is responsible for maintaining the status information of both the environment and the agents (Figure 2)."
  ]
}